Samsung South Africa has launched a new door-to-door repair service for smartphones, tablets, and wearables. Instead of visiting one of the companyâ€™s customer care centres, Samsung device owners will now be able to request a repair online, have their device collected at home or their office, and then returned again once it is fixed. The pick-up and return service is priced at R330, not including the cost of the repair itself. Samsung said the service will be available to addresses within 40km of one of its customer care centres. To use the service, follow these steps: Due to COVID-19 regulations, the product will be sanitised and packaged before the customer. Samsung said the following devices will be eligible for repair via the service: Smartphones Tablets Wearables